Enum Class SzFlagUsageGroup

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<SzFlagUsageGroup>
com.senzing.sdk.SzFlagUsageGroup
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<SzFlagUsageGroup>, Constable
public enum SzFlagUsageGroup extends Enum<SzFlagUsageGroup>
Enumerates the various classifications of usage groups for the SzFlag instances.

4.0.0

    • SZ_ADD_RECORD_FLAGS

      public static final SzFlagUsageGroup SZ_ADD_RECORD_FLAGS
      Flags in this usage group can be used for operations that add records to the entity repository. Applicable methods include:
      • SzEngine.addRecord(SzRecordKey, String, Set)

      The SzFlag instances included in this usage group are:

      4.0.0

    • toString

      public String toString(long flagsValue)
      Formats the String representation of the specified long flags value according to the SzFlag instances included for this SzFlagUsageGroup.

      NOTE: This method is useful in logging which flags were past to a particular method using the SzFlagUsageGroup for the flags that are accepted by that method.

      Some SzFlag values have the same underlying bitwise flag value, but none of the SzFlag instances for a single SzFlagUsageGroup should overlap in bitwise values and this method will prefer the SzFlag belonging to this SzFlagUsageGroup for formatting the String.

      Parameters:
      flagsValue - The long flags to format as a String.
      Returns:
      The String describing the specified flags.
      Since:
      4.0.0

    • toFlagSet

      public Set<SzFlag> toFlagSet(long flagsValue)
      Creates a Set of SzFlag instances representing the flags for the corresponding bit flags in the specified long value according to the SzFlag instances included for this SzFlagUsageGroup.

      Some SzFlag values have the same underlying bitwise flag value, but none of the SzFlag instances for a single SzFlagUsageGroup should overlap in bitwise values and this method will prefer the SzFlag belonging to this SzFlagUsageGroup for inclusion in the returned Set.

      Parameters:
      flagsValue - The long flags to convert to a Set of SzFlag instances.
      Returns:
      The Set of SzFlag instances for the specified long value.
      Since:
      4.0.0
